Citation: Herrera, S. Samples collected aboard 2017 RESTORE Cruise aboard MSV Ocean Project (OP17).
Repository: Lehigh University
IdentifiedBy: Herrera, Santiago | Quattrini, Andrea | Etnoyer, Peter | Sanchez, Juan | Galaska, Matt | Shuler, Andrew | Frometa, Janessy
IdentificationQualifier: ID based on DNA barcode and gross morphology
LocationComments: Difference from CRM: 26m | original LocationAccuracy reported as 10m
Purpose: population connectivity
SurveyComments: The cruise was dedicated to finding and sampling corals for the study entitled 'Population Connectivity of Deepwater Corals in the Northern Gulf of Mexico' funded by NOAA RESTORE Science program. Individual counts and photo-images do not represent a census of corals, they represent a few target species and our collections for those species. IndividualCounts are always shown as '1', but many colonies may occur in any one image. No transects were conducted, and no attempts were made to quantify abundance.

IdentifiedBy: Herrera, Santiago | Quattrini, Andrea | Etnoyer, Peter | Sanchez, Juan | Galaska, Matt | Shuler, Andrew | Frometa, Janessy
IdentificationQualifier: ID based on DNA barcode and gross morphology
LocationComments: Difference from CRM: 13m | original LocationAccuracy reported as 10m
Purpose: population connectivity
SurveyComments: The cruise was dedicated to finding and sampling corals for the study entitled 'Population Connectivity of Deepwater Corals in the Northern Gulf of Mexico' funded by NOAA RESTORE Science program. Individual counts and photo-images do not represent a census of corals, they represent a few target species and our collections for those species. IndividualCounts are always shown as '1', but many colonies may occur in any one image. No transects were conducted, and no attempts were made to quantify abundance.
